cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR

This paper deals with the collection and analysis of a large dataset for behavioral biometrics, specifically typing, gait, and swipe performed by the same person on multiple devices. The paper discusses the challenges in collecting such a dataset and the potential research directions enabled by it. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with user authentication, and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves the use of multiple devices by the same person. It may also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the analysis of accelerometer and gyroscope data, and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the analysis of keystroke data.
